# Usage Examples

### Random Supported Game

```javascript
async function loadRandomGame() {
  await HRN.init();

  const game = HRN
    .search('mario')
    .filterSupported()
    .random()
    .list[0];

  if (game) {
    console.log(`Suggested: ${game.name}`);
  }
}
```

### Favorites Discovery

```javascript
async function getDiscoveryList() {
  const favorites = HRN
    .reset()
    .filterFavorites()
    .random(3)
    .list;
}
```

# Favorites System

Favorites are stored automatically using LocalStorage, allowing users to persist their favorite games across sessions.

---

### Toggle Favorite

Add or remove a game from favorites using its alias.

```javascript
HRN.toggleFavorite('mario');
```

---

### Check Favorite Status

```javascript
if (HRN.isFavorite('mario')) {
  console.log('Mario is a favorite');
}
```

---

### Get All Favorite Games

```javascript
const favorites = HRN
  .reset()
  .filterFavorites()
  .list;

console.log(favorites);
```

---

### Random Favorite Game

```javascript
const game = HRN
  .reset()
  .filterFavorites()
  .random()
  .list[0];

if (game) {
  console.log(`Play this: ${game.name}`);
}
```

---

### Remove All Favorites (Manual Reset)

```javascript
HRN.list.forEach(game => {
  if (game.isFavorite) {
    HRN.toggleFavorite(game.alias);
  }
});
```

---

### UI Example (Toggle Button)

```javascript
function toggleFav(alias) {
  HRN.toggleFavorite(alias);

  const isFav = HRN.isFavorite(alias);
  console.log(isFav ? 'Added to favorites' : 'Removed from favorites');
}
```

---

### Notes

* Favorites persist via LocalStorage.
* Works instantly without reloading.
* Can be combined with filters, search, and randomization.

```javascript
// Example combo
const picks = HRN
  .search('kart')
  .filterFavorites()
  .random(2)
  .list;
```
